In analogy to the right eigenvectors, the series again appears to be not
 only convergent in that 
\begin_inset Formula $\lim_{n\to\infty}w_{kn}=0$
\end_inset

, but also that a strict ratio is maintained in the limit: 
\begin_inset Formula $\lim_{n\to\infty}(n+2)\, w_{kn}/(n+1)\, w_{k,n+1}=1$
\end_inset

, with strict equality holding for all 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

, and not just in the limit, when 
\begin_inset Formula $k=0$
\end_inset

.
 A similar oscillatory behaviour is seen as well, as shown in figure 
